    	</div>

    	<div class="comment_content">
    		<p>Thanks for insights on a very difficult &#8211; but necessary &#8211; discussion.</p>
<p>You describe choices that all except the most lucky among us will probably face.</p>
<p>We all need to think about this topic while it is still an intellectual discussion.  Once the imminence of death starts to intrude, emotion (fear, despair, sense of loss, hope), will cloud our judgement &#8211; even for the bravest and clearest minded among us.</p>
<p>And others with different opinions may try to influence us when we are at our weakest.</p>
<p>Our families will feel everything that we feel, plus guilt and the intrusion of their own value systems.  We owe our families guidance/clarity when they speak about our futures.</p>
<p>Plus, I would hate for them to make the wrong choices.</p>

    	</div>

